author: @kameshparashar
text: What In personally think is that, ANN's are useful for regression problems for big datasets. But they are not much accurate when it comes for CLASSIFICATION of TABULAR DATA. But deep learning is best for NPL, Image, Text processing etc. So long ans short: If you're in a hackathon which is regression with huge data use Deep learning. But most of the hackathons are Classification of tabular data, if thats the case use ML models. My personal fav is LightGBM.

From your point of view and from my knowledge in the field of IT and Machine learning and Deep learning, I have some conclusions, someone may not agree.  01. You said that Machine Learning is normally / usually applied on small data sets. As day by day volume of data is increasing having exponential growth. And number of data generators are also increasing ultimately results in increase in volume of data. e.g Iot devices, Youtube channels, patient's data, insurance data, bank's data and many more like these. So in near future volume of data will be very large in every case and so ultimately Machine Learning will be only theory. 02. I have a core 2 do system with 4 GB RAM and 180 GB SSD without any other storage but I am using GPU on google colab. 03.
